    <section class="about-section" id="about">
        <div class="about-content">
            <h2>// Why HTML Matters</h2>
            <p>HTML (HyperText Markup Language) is the standard markup language for creating web pages. It describes the structure of a web page and consists of a series of elements.</p>
            <p>HTML elements tell the browser how to display the content. From headings and paragraphs to links, images, and interactive forms—HTML is the backbone of every website on the internet.</p>
            <p>Unlike programming languages, HTML is a markup language that defines the structure of your content. Combined with CSS for styling and JavaScript for interactivity, you have the complete web development stack.</p>
            <p><strong>The web starts with HTML. Now you can build it.</strong></p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="resources-section" id="resources">
        <h2>// Tools & References</h2>
        <div class="resources-grid">
            <div class="resource-card">
